cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS

The paper focuses on developing unsupervised relevance-based word embedding models for information retrieval tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper also discusses natural language processing tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper proposes two learning models with different objective functions, which involves classification and distribution, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of word2vec and GloVe, which are popular embedding models, suggesting that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses over six million unique queries and evaluates the models on two IR tasks, indicating that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
